-- TASK 1:  
Create an IAM group named Developers. 
Create two IAM users, dev-user1 and dev-user2 and enable MFA. 
Attach the AmazonEC2ReadOnlyAccess policy to the Developers group. 
Attach the BillingReadOnlyAccess policy to the Developers group. 
Add dev-user1 and dev-user2 to the Developers group. 
Confirm that dev-user1 and dev-user2 can only view EC2 instances and access the Billing dashboard but cannot make any changes.

TASK -1 
Create a S3 bucket and host a static website of Nginx through S3 feature after that integrate cloudFront service with your S3 bucket to overcome the latency and then access your static website through cloudFront url. Now change the content and hit again remember cache will not be taken at that time 
Things you will learn: 
S3 
S3 policy 
Object policy 
cloudFront 
Nginx 
invalidation option


TASK-2 
Create a Instance inside VPC network if already exist if not then make whole infrastructure with the help of aws-cli tool 
Perform operations below through aws-cli: 
Start instance 
Stop instance 
Restart instance 
Terminate instance 
Attach IAM role to that instance 
Make ALB internet facing 
Good to do, If above implemented then implement this by aws-cli with single click, first do manually on console.
